cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IT, cs.DS, cs.CC 

This paper discusses the role of bias in machine learning and search algorithms, which is a central topic in the field of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also touches on information theory (cs.IT) and computational complexity (cs.CC) in its discussion of the difficulty of finding a favorably biasing distribution. Additionally, the paper uses mathematical and geometric concepts, which are often studied in the field of data science (cs.DS).
